# Be VERY MINDFUL when making changes to how the config, config structure, feature flags, feature flag structure works

## About the config 

Remember, that a `config.js` shall be provided by the user themselves and created later on in the same build folder (`*/dist/config.js`)
`RelativeDistConfigPlugin` exists so that all of the files that are trying to get the confic inside of AeroSandbox. an reference the user created `config.js` (in the dist folder), which is extended from defaultConfig.js. An example of the user extending this would be in `src/AeroSandbox/examples/config.js`
This lets the user reconfigure the proxy and sandboxer without having to rebuild

## About the feature flags

*Unlike the config*, the **Feature Flags are for removing or adding functionality at build-time, making some things not configurable by the user later, in favor of saving build size**. This philosophy is also why shared builds are an option and why minimal builds should exist. It is also why there is configuration in the builds, which gives way to things like `AeroSandboxBuilder`. That is why to use AeroSandbox, you are recommended provide a custom build, instead of using a full blanket, everything enabled build.